President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of California due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This declaration allows for Federal assistance to supplement State, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for Crisis Counseling for affected individuals, as well as emergency protective measures for all areas impacted by COVID-19. Robert J. Fenton has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made in the future based on assessments and requests from the State. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.